### CHAPTER LV <span id="fr_1368"></span>[6](#fn_1357.md).

1\. The fifty-fifth subject is this, that when a Navazû*d* <span
id="fr_1369"></span>[7](#fn_1358.md) *ceremony* is performed, and it
happens that it is not possible to consecrate a sacred cake, it is
necessary that *one should* eat bread with the Hôrmazd *inward* prayer;
*and*, afterwards, he *should*

<span id="page_317">p. 317</span>

complete the prayer just as when they complete *it* as regards the
sacred cake, so that the sin *may* be less.

